unittitle_ssm: Records of the Office of the Dean of the Tisch School of the Arts
abstract_ssm: The Tisch School of the Arts (TSOA) was founded as a school of performing and media arts in 1965. Alumni include Spike Lee, Oliver Stone, Amy Heckerling, and Ang Lee. Much of the school's history is documented in the correspondence of the School's former Deans, Robert Oppenheim and Robert Corrigan, and former Professor Theodore Hoffman. Additional records in the collection include annual reports, budgets, financial records, minutes, curricula, scripts and press clippings.
